{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Dial-EditConform\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script comes after FieldrecorderTrackmatching to automate dialogue audio conforming:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Creating tracks from iXML/BWF metadata,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Exploding multichannel items into separate mono tracks (thanks to RODILAB for this),\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Renaming items according to their source and metadata,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Moving items to appropriate tracks based on take names,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Deleting empty tracks or tracks containing only items/takes named "DISARMED".\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ends by deselecting all items and tracks for a clean state.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Advanced dialogue track conforming and organizing (iXML/BWF metadata, splitting, renaming, moving, cleaning).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script was developed with the help of GitHub Copilot.\par}
}

